How climate change is driving winter weather patterns in Ohio
<https://click.communications.case.edu/?qs=402364c1a5dac724a1a604164a4a84592ff5ffad8873f8eb3bf2624e36f56484317102f82b2aac453e601d094b96ccf8b4b1f8eda752a8f6b88120b64f415092>

Climate change has had a notable impact on our planet’s weather, from
prompting an increase in tropical storms to spurring melting ice caps.
Those issues may seem far from Cleveland, but our region experiences global
warming in its own ways—even if this week’s blast of frigid temperatures
seems to indicate otherwise. To better understand how climate change has
affected the wintry conditions we’re accustomed to in Northeast Ohio, we
spoke with Peter Whiting, interim dean of the College of Arts and Sciences,
professor and director of the Environmental Studies Program.

[image: Media Mentions]
Landlord overcharged renters hundreds of millions in junk fees for years,
alleges FTC lawsuit
<https://click.communications.case.edu/?qs=402364c1a5dac72434a475cc0738412219dbefcf1f825375d76e3d89e8333b533ade725ef4e2ba48aabf1310e0af094ef84bc95b66c602b48d49a846f908054c>

*Fortune Magazine*: *Cathy Mansfield*, senior instructor in law,
highlighted the burden of hidden rental fees. “My kids are paying for
regular and concierge garbage pickup—despite not needing both,” she said.
As lawsuits like the FTC’s case against Greystar grow, she stressed knowing
your rights and questioning unclear charges.
With Husted in the U.S. Senate, which Republicans are positioning
themselves to be Ohio’s next governor?
<https://click.communications.case.edu/?qs=402364c1a5dac7244e8856742e6ae5a03be25ea8abdcbde4ccb1345347e556d4bdfeb4ef0c67abd317fd27499dc36776941c85ad5ba6e846382fa6aa9df6dd9b>

*cleveland.com <http://cleveland.com>* (subscription required): *Justin
Buchler*, associate professor of political science at the College of Arts
and Sciences, noted that the 2026 Ohio governor’s race features a
competitive GOP primary between Vivek Ramaswamy, Robert Sprague and Dave
Yost. Buchler said that while experience often prevails, “in a three-way
campaign, that rule holds less often,” making an upset possible with a
split vote.
Experts address Trump pardoning almost all Jan. 6 rioters, including about
80 Ohioans
<https://click.communications.case.edu/?qs=402364c1a5dac724995c7fe07054b72b13a31913b0755128f7d6f56a54fd0f7f878e4b0ac6bd0ccd2b531706d9dfe5509b638376a29711e4c87f13ec74fbef89>

*Spectrum News*: *Jonathan Entin*, the David L. Brennan Professor Emeritus
of Law, discussed President Donald Trump’s pardons of Jan. 6 participants,
including Ohioan Jared Kastner.
Fiber may help protect your gut against infections
<https://click.communications.case.edu/?qs=402364c1a5dac7242e317043bf0c5e1e9bda981117b1c06544f526ca0a11bce136fb1c525f1739dbf2f490267fb070bf25cb5e5797dd04822615d3efb96c9e91>

*Everyday Health*: *Mahmoud Ghannoum*, professor at the School of Medicine,
discussed a new study's emphasis on fiber as a prebiotic. “This research
reinforces the need for fiber-rich diets to rebalance and sustain a healthy
microbiome,” Ghannoum said, underscoring its potential to reduce harmful
bacteria and prevent gut infections.
